         <div type="translation">
            <p> To the divine spirits. Decimus Annius Rufus, a soldier of the praetorian Fleet of
               Ravenna, Dalmatian by origin, lived for thirty-five years and served as a soldier for
               fourteen years. Publius Camurius Campanus, [his] heir, made [this] for his
               well-deserving friend.</p>
         </div>
